# AI-Assisted Development

## Core Philosophy

> AI is a **multiplier**, not a replacement. Use it to amplify your skills, not bypass learning.

---

## Effective Prompting Patterns

### The CONTEXT-TASK-RULES Pattern

```
I'm building [CONTEXT - what you're working on].
I need to [SPECIFIC TASK - be precise].
Here's my current code: [CODE or file reference].
Following these rules: [@coding-standards.mdc, @error-handling.mdc].
What's the best approach and why?
```

### Good vs Bad Prompts

| ‚ùå Bad            | ‚úÖ Good                                                                                                                  |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| "Write a service" | "Create a NestJS service method that bulk-creates seats for a venue, with transaction support and proper error handling" |
| "Fix this bug"    | "This method throws 'Cannot read property X'. Here's the code and stack trace. What's the root cause?"                   |
| "Make it better"  | "Review this code for: 1) N+1 queries, 2) Missing error handling, 3) Violations of our coding-standards.mdc"             |

