## Code Review Checklist for AI Code

Before accepting AI-generated code, verify:

### Architecture

- [ ] Follows our `coding-standards.mdc`
- [ ] Respects module boundaries
- [ ] Uses proper dependency injection
- [ ] Doesn't introduce circular dependencies

### Error Handling

- [ ] Follows `error-handling.mdc`
- [ ] Throws appropriate exceptions
- [ ] Handles edge cases
- [ ] Doesn't swallow errors silently

### Security

- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
- [ ] Input validation present
- [ ] SQL injection safe (parameterized queries)
- [ ] No exposed internal details in errors

### Performance

- [ ] No N+1 queries
- [ ] Appropriate use of transactions
- [ ] No memory leaks (streams for large data)
- [ ] Pagination for lists

### Testing

- [ ] Code is testable (dependencies injectable)
- [ ] Edge cases identified
- [ ] Error paths covered

